parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the Takata airbag recall can lead to a heightened risk of injury or death to occupants in the event of an accident, as the faulty airbags may not deploy properly or may deploy with excessive force.
symptoms: as the issue is related to the recall repair delay rather than a specific symptom.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to serious injury or death to occupants.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy in an accident

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of the airbag can cause injuries to occupants, and may also lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Airbag deployment without an accident or collision
resulting in injuries or damage to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust manifold bolts can cause exhaust gas to leak into the passenger compartment, potentially leading to a fire, and affect engine performance, causing stalling or loss of power.
symptoms: exhaust gas leaking into the passenger compartment
engine stalling or loss of power

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling or Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling or loss of power can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially when towing.
symptoms: inability to accelerate above first gear

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column Intermediate Shaft Rattling Noise
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rattling noise in the intermediate shaft of the steering column can cause distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Rattling noise in the steering column

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Wheel Shaking and Loose Tie Rod
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The shaking of the steering wheel can cause loss of control, especially when turning or drifting, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Steering wheel shakes slightly but noticeably at any speed
feels worse when turning or drifting right
left wheel seems tighter and not as loose
right wheel is noticeably loose with slight noise indicative of a loose or worn tie rod.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
